CatDescriptText: Donn Clendenon, number 17, was the Pittsburgh Pirate's first baseman 1961-1968. He led the 1969 NY Mets to the World Series Championship and became WS MVP.  He then went on to Duquesne Law School in 1974 to become a player agent. Here he is standing on the grass at Forbes Field posing as if ready to bunt.
TitMainTitle: Pittsburgh Pirates baseball players no. 8 Willie Stargell, and no. 17 Donn Clendenon, posing with bats in bunting position, on Forbes Field
